snippet: Boeing said on Thursday that it delivered 762 jetliners in 2015, exceeding its target of 755 to 760 planes.
abstract: Boeing announces it delivered 762 jetliners in 2015, exceeding year’s goal and beating Airbus Group for distinction as world’s leading aircraft manufacturer.
lead_paragraph: Boeing said on Thursday that it delivered 762 jetliners in 2015, exceeding its target of 755 to 760 planes.

headline.print_headline: Boeing Exceeds 2015 Forecasts, Most Likely Topping Airbus
headline.main: Boeing Exceeds 2015 Forecasts, Most Likely Topping Airbus
